The recuerd0 CLI — your terminal, your memories

Everything in the web UI, available from your terminal. Install with one command:

  brew install recuerd0/tap/recuerd0

Or download directly from the releases page:
https://github.com/maquina-app/recuerd0-cli/releases

Quick example:

  # Set your API token
  export RECUERD0_TOKEN="your-token-here"
  export RECUERD0_HOST="<%= root_url.chomp("/") %>"

  # List your workspaces
  recuerd0 workspace list --pretty

  # Search across everything
  recuerd0 search "deployment config" --pretty

The CLI supports everything — workspaces, memories, search, versioning — all from the command line.

CLI Reference: https://github.com/maquina-app/recuerd0-cli

Pair the CLI with shell scripts or CI pipelines to automate your knowledge workflows.
